snippet.textDisplay: Sam O'Nella is that one friend that we all had back in high school where his sense of humor was 10 years ahead. Sometimes his jokes went over some of the kid's head, but he threw in some slapstick humor here & there to not let himself get too high-brow. He was one of the few kids who managed to get a "B" while everyone else got an "A" in art class. He was in AP US government, & he was that kid that never had to study in AP History b/c he breezed through various history books/videos. He tried to get acquainted with one of his AP History teachers but alienated the teacher when Sam vividly told stories about the French man, Tararre; "Just finish the packet by tomorrow, Sam." His senior AP History teacher was more supportive though, and that's how we have the historian Sam O'Nella today.
